# NairaX Demo – Setup Guide

## Files
- `index.html` – Main app shell + all screens & modals
- `style.css` – All styles (OPay-inspired mobile UI)
- `app.js` – All logic: auth, wallet, send, crypto, bills, DB
- `manifest.json` – PWA manifest (add to home screen)

## How to Run

### Option 1: Local (quick test)
Just open `index.html` in Chrome/Firefox on your phone or desktop.

### Option 2: Host on GitHub Pages (free, sharable link)
1. Create a GitHub repo, upload all 4 files to root
2. Go to Settings → Pages → Deploy from branch (main / root)
3. Your app is live at: `https://yourusername.github.io/repo-name`
4. Share the link and open on Android → tap "Add to Home Screen"

### Option 3: Host on Netlify (free, instant)
1. Go to netlify.com → "Deploy manually"
2. Drag and drop the folder with all 4 files
3. Get a live URL instantly

---

## Add to Android Home Screen (PWA)
1. Open the URL in Chrome on Android
2. Tap the 3-dot menu → "Add to Home screen"
3. App will open fullscreen like a native app

---

## Demo Features
- **Signup/Login** with phone number + 4-digit PIN
- **₦100,000 test Naira** credited on signup
- **EVM wallet** auto-generated from your phone number
- **Send to bank**: simulates fee calculation (0.75% on crypto→naira sends)
- **Send to NairaX user**: free naira-to-naira between test accounts
- **Crypto deposit simulation**: click "Simulate Deposit" on Crypto tab
  - Adds 0.026 sETH (~₦98,800) to your balance
  - Shows breakdown in Assets section
- **Bills**: Airtime, Data, Electricity, Cable TV (all deduct from balance)
- **Multi-device**: data saved to localStorage, same phone = same wallet
- **Transaction history**: full log with timestamps

---

## Architecture Notes (for investor pitch)
- Frontend: Vanilla JS + CSS (no framework = fast, lightweight)
- Storage: localStorage (demo) → swap for Firebase/Supabase in production
- Wallets: deterministic generation (demo) → use ethers.js + secure key storage in production
- Crypto pricing: hardcoded rate (demo) → use Binance/CoinGecko API in production
- Pool model: company holds naira + crypto → pays out naira when user sends, accumulates crypto